Note:
PROTOBUF DESCRIPTOR - Foundational AST for .proto Files (Tier 1)

Implements the Runa-native AST for Protocol Buffers descriptors. The
shape mirrors google.protobuf.FileDescriptorProto from descriptor.proto
(https://github.com/protocolbuffers/protobuf/blob/main/src/google/protobuf/descriptor.proto)
so binary FileDescriptorSet payloads emitted by protoc round-trip
through this representation.

SCOPE OF THIS MODULE:
  - Construct/destroy ProtobufFile, ProtobufMessage, ProtobufField,
    ProtobufEnum, ProtobufService AST nodes.
  - Provide field accessors and append helpers used by all downstream
    consumers (the protoc-binary decoder, the .proto-text parser, the
    Runa-to-proto codegen, the proto-to-Runa adapter).

FUTURE FILL (deliberately deferred):
  - The .proto-text grammar lexer/parser is a large surface (option
    blocks, custom options, extension ranges, reserved fields,
    oneofs with tagged unions). The AST is complete and stable here;
    the .proto-text producer that populates these records lives in
    a Tier 2 package (runa-protobuf-toolchain) because it requires
    the regex engine and unicode-NFC normalizer.
  - The protoc binary descriptor decoder reads the same AST and is
    tracked separately so its varint/length-prefix machinery does
    not bloat this file.

Layout (ProtobufFile, 56 bytes):
  offset  0 : syntax        (8 bytes, see SYNTAX_* constants)
  offset  8 : package       (8 bytes, String pointer or 0)
  offset 16 : imports       (8 bytes, List<String>)
  offset 24 : messages      (8 bytes, List<ProtobufMessage>)
  offset 32 : enums         (8 bytes, List<ProtobufEnum>)
  offset 40 : services      (8 bytes, List<ProtobufService>)
  offset 48 : file_options  (8 bytes, Dictionary<String, ConfigValue> or 0)

Layout (ProtobufMessage, 56 bytes):
  offset  0 : name          (8 bytes, String pointer)
  offset  8 : fields        (8 bytes, List<ProtobufField>)
  offset 16 : nested_messages (8 bytes, List<ProtobufMessage>)
  offset 24 : nested_enums  (8 bytes, List<ProtobufEnum>)
  offset 32 : oneofs        (8 bytes, List<String> - oneof group names)
  offset 40 : reserved_numbers (8 bytes, List<Integer>)
  offset 48 : reserved_names    (8 bytes, List<String>)

Layout (ProtobufField, 48 bytes):
  offset  0 : name          (8 bytes, String pointer)
  offset  8 : field_number  (8 bytes, 1..536870911 per spec)
  offset 16 : type_tag      (8 bytes, see PB_TYPE_*)
  offset 24 : type_name     (8 bytes, String pointer for message/enum types or 0)
  offset 32 : label         (8 bytes, see PB_LABEL_*)
  offset 40 : json_name     (8 bytes, String pointer or 0)

Layout (ProtobufEnum, 24 bytes):
  offset  0 : name          (8 bytes, String pointer)
  offset  8 : values        (8 bytes, List<EnumValue 16 bytes>)
  offset 16 : allow_alias   (8 bytes, 0 or 1)
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrim
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dict

Let PB_FILE_SIZE be 56
Let PB_MESSAGE_SIZE be 56
Let PB_FIELD_SIZE be 48
Let PB_ENUM_SIZE be 24

Let SYNTAX_PROTO2 be 2
Let SYNTAX_PROTO3 be 3

Note: Wire-format type tags per descriptor.proto.
Let PB_TYPE_DOUBLE be 1
Let PB_TYPE_FLOAT be 2
Let PB_TYPE_INT64 be 3
Let PB_TYPE_UINT64 be 4
Let PB_TYPE_INT32 be 5
Let PB_TYPE_FIXED64 be 6
Let PB_TYPE_FIXED32 be 7
Let PB_TYPE_BOOL be 8
Let PB_TYPE_STRING be 9
Let PB_TYPE_GROUP be 10
Let PB_TYPE_MESSAGE be 11
Let PB_TYPE_BYTES be 12
Let PB_TYPE_UINT32 be 13
Let PB_TYPE_ENUM be 14
Let PB_TYPE_SFIXED32 be 15
Let PB_TYPE_SFIXED64 be 16
Let PB_TYPE_SINT32 be 17
Let PB_TYPE_SINT64 be 18

Let PB_LABEL_OPTIONAL be 1
Let PB_LABEL_REQUIRED be 2
Let PB_LABEL_REPEATED be 3

@Reasoning
Construct a ProtobufFile with the given syntax. Pre-allocates the
collection slots.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate the 56-byte record. Create empty lists for imports,
messages, enums, services. Set the syntax tag.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1) plus the empty collection headers.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure or invalid syntax tag.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pb_file_create" takes syntax as Integer returns Integer:
    If syntax is less than SYNTAX_PROTO2:
        Return 0
    End If
    If syntax is greater than SYNTAX_PROTO3:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let f be proc allocate from Layout with PB_FILE_SIZE
    If f is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let imports be proc list_create from List
    Let messages be proc list_create from List
    Let enums be proc list_create from List
    Let services be proc list_create from List
    If imports is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with f
        Return 0
    End If
    If messages is equal to 0:
        proc list_destroy from List with imports
        proc deallocate from Layout with f
        Return 0
    End If
    If enums is equal to 0:
        proc list_destroy from List with messages
        proc list_destroy from List with imports
        proc deallocate from Layout with f
        Return 0
    End If
    If services is equal to 0:
        proc list_destroy from List with enums
        proc list_destroy from List with messages
        proc list_destroy from List with imports
        proc deallocate from Layout with f
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 0, syntax
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 8, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 16, imports
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 24, messages
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 32, enums
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 40, services
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 48, 0
    Return f
End Process

@Reasoning
Construct a ProtobufMessage. Pre-allocates collection slots.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 56 bytes, populate name (duplicated), create empty
collections.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|name|). Space: O(|name|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null name.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pb_message_create" takes name as Integer returns Integer:
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let name_copy be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with name
    If name_copy is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let m be proc allocate from Layout with PB_MESSAGE_SIZE
    If m is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with name_copy
        Return 0
    End If
    Let fields be proc list_create from List
    Let nested_m be proc list_create from List
    Let nested_e be proc list_create from List
    Let oneofs be proc list_create from List
    Let reserved_n be proc list_create from List
    Let reserved_s be proc list_create from List
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with m, 0, name_copy
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with m, 8, fields
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with m, 16, nested_m
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with m, 24, nested_e
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with m, 32, oneofs
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with m, 40, reserved_n
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with m, 48, reserved_s
    Return m
End Process

@Reasoning
Construct a ProtobufField. The type_name applies only to message /
enum type tags; pass 0 for scalar types.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Validate the field_number against the protobuf reserved range
[19000..19999] and the absolute max 536870911. Allocate 48 bytes,
populate.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|name|). Space: O(|name|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Reserved-range numbers (19000..19999) and out-of-range numbers
return 0.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pb_field_create" takes name as Integer, field_number as Integer, type_tag as Integer, type_name as Integer, label as Integer returns Integer:
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If field_number is less than 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    If field_number is greater than 536870911:
        Return 0
    End If
    If field_number is greater than or equal to 19000:
        If field_number is less than or equal to 19999:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If
    If type_tag is less than PB_TYPE_DOUBLE:
        Return 0
    End If
    If type_tag is greater than PB_TYPE_SINT64:
        Return 0
    End If
    If label is less than PB_LABEL_OPTIONAL:
        Return 0
    End If
    If label is greater than PB_LABEL_REPEATED:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let name_copy be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with name
    If name_copy is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let type_name_copy be 0
    If type_name is not equal to 0:
        Set type_name_copy to proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with type_name
    End If
    Let f be proc allocate from Layout with PB_FIELD_SIZE
    If f is equal to 0:
        If type_name_copy is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with type_name_copy
        End If
        proc deallocate from Layout with name_copy
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 0, name_copy
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 8, field_number
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 16, type_tag
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 24, type_name_copy
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 32, label
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 40, 0
    Return f
End Process

@Reasoning
Construct a ProtobufEnum.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Duplicate the name, allocate, create an empty values list.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|name|). Space: O(|name|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null name.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pb_enum_create" takes name as Integer returns Integer:
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let name_copy be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with name
    If name_copy is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let vals be proc list_create from List
    If vals is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with name_copy
        Return 0
    End If
    Let e be proc allocate from Layout with PB_ENUM_SIZE
    If e is equal to 0:
        proc list_destroy from List with vals
        proc deallocate from Layout with name_copy
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with e, 0, name_copy
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with e, 8, vals
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with e, 16, 0
    Return e
End Process

@Reasoning
Append a message to a file.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
list_push into the messages slot.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: amortized O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The file adopts the message; release via pb_file_destroy.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pb_file_add_message" takes f as Integer, m as Integer returns Integer:
    If f is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If m is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let list be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 24
    proc list_push from List with list, m
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Append a field to a message.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
list_push.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: amortized O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The message adopts the field.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pb_message_add_field" takes m as Integer, field as Integer returns Integer:
    If m is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If field is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let list be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with m, 8
    proc list_push from List with list, field
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Append an enum to a file.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
list_push.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: amortized O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The file adopts the enum.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pb_file_add_enum" takes f as Integer, e as Integer returns Integer:
    If f is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If e is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let list be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 32
    proc list_push from List with list, e
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Free a ProtobufField and its owned strings.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Free name and (if present) type_name, then the record.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller must not access the pointer after destroy.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pb_field_destroy" takes f as Integer returns Integer:
    If f is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let name be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 0
    If name is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with name
    End If
    Let tn be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 24
    If tn is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with tn
    End If
    Let jn be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 40
    If jn is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with jn
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with f
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Free a ProtobufMessage and all nested elements.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk every nested collection, deallocating fields and recursing into
nested messages / enums.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over the message subtree. Space: O(d) recursion.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller must not access the pointer after destroy.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pb_message_destroy" takes m as Integer returns Integer:
    If m is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let name be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with m, 0
    If name is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with name
    End If
    Let fields be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with m, 8
    If fields is not equal to 0:
        Let fn be proc list_length from List with fields
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than fn:
            Let fld be proc list_get from List with fields, i
            If fld is not equal to 0:
                proc pb_field_destroy with fld
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with fields
    End If
    Let nm be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with m, 16
    If nm is not equal to 0:
        Let nm_n be proc list_length from List with nm
        Let j be 0
        While j is less than nm_n:
            Let child be proc list_get from List with nm, j
            If child is not equal to 0:
                proc pb_message_destroy with child
            End If
            Set j to j plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with nm
    End If
    Let ne be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with m, 24
    If ne is not equal to 0:
        Let ne_n be proc list_length from List with ne
        Let k be 0
        While k is less than ne_n:
            Let e be proc list_get from List with ne, k
            If e is not equal to 0:
                proc pb_enum_destroy with e
            End If
            Set k to k plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with ne
    End If
    Let oneofs be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with m, 32
    If oneofs is not equal to 0:
        proc list_destroy from List with oneofs
    End If
    Let rn be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with m, 40
    If rn is not equal to 0:
        proc list_destroy from List with rn
    End If
    Let rs be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with m, 48
    If rs is not equal to 0:
        proc list_destroy from List with rs
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with m
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Free a ProtobufEnum and its values list.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Free name; iterate values list freeing each entry; destroy the list;
free the record.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(v) for the value count. Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller must not access the pointer after destroy.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pb_enum_destroy" takes e as Integer returns Integer:
    If e is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let name be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with e, 0
    If name is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with name
    End If
    Let vals be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with e, 8
    If vals is not equal to 0:
        Let vn be proc list_length from List with vals
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than vn:
            Let v be proc list_get from List with vals, i
            If v is not equal to 0:
                proc deallocate from Layout with v
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with vals
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with e
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Free a ProtobufFile and every owned subtree.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Iterate messages calling pb_message_destroy, enums calling
pb_enum_destroy. Free imports and services lists, package string,
options dict.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over the whole file. Space: O(d) recursion.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller must not access the pointer after destroy.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pb_file_destroy" takes f as Integer returns Integer:
    If f is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let package be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 8
    If package is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with package
    End If
    Let imports be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 16
    If imports is not equal to 0:
        Let in_n be proc list_length from List with imports
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than in_n:
            Let s be proc list_get from List with imports, i
            If s is not equal to 0:
                proc deallocate from Layout with s
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with imports
    End If
    Let messages be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 24
    If messages is not equal to 0:
        Let mn be proc list_length from List with messages
        Let j be 0
        While j is less than mn:
            Let m be proc list_get from List with messages, j
            If m is not equal to 0:
                proc pb_message_destroy with m
            End If
            Set j to j plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with messages
    End If
    Let enums be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 32
    If enums is not equal to 0:
        Let en be proc list_length from List with enums
        Let k be 0
        While k is less than en:
            Let e be proc list_get from List with enums, k
            If e is not equal to 0:
                proc pb_enum_destroy with e
            End If
            Set k to k plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with enums
    End If
    Let services be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 40
    If services is not equal to 0:
        proc list_destroy from List with services
    End If
    Let opts be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 48
    If opts is not equal to 0:
        proc destroy from Dict with opts
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with f
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the file's syntax discriminator.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pb_file_syntax" takes f as Integer returns Integer:
    If f is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 0
End Process

